Six persons died and one other injured in yet another auto crash on the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway on Wednesday. The crash at Kara turning point came few hours after a Toyota Hiace bus went up in flames, killing four persons and injuring 13 others at Fidiwo area of Ogunmakin on the expressway. Federal Road Safety Corps spokesperson, Florence Okpe, said the latest accident involved a Toyota Previa marked LRG 165 AA. Ms Okpe said that eight persons were involved in the accident, adding that it was caused by excessive speeding and loss of control which led to the vehicle hitting the road median. She said the injured victim was taken to Redeemed Hospital for treatment, while the deceased were deposited at a hospital in Sagamu, Ogun. (NAN) Donate TEXT AD: To place an advert here . Call Willie - +2348098788999 <img style="max-width: 100%; height: auto; align: center;" src="https://i2.wp.com/media.premiumtimesng.com/wp-content/files/2019/06/pt-magazine-advert.gif?ssl=1" alt="PT Mag Campaign AD" data-recalc-dims="1" />